{"kind":"cas-record-v1","metadata":{"entries":[{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/gocas","identifier":"RootDirForBaseDir","question":"For checking internal/cli SPEC conformance: what CAS root selection rules does RootDirForBaseDir implement, including behavior for CODALOTL_CAS_DB, git repos/worktrees, and fallback?","answer":"`RootDirForBaseDir` implements these CAS root rules on the `gocas` side:\n\n- `CODALOTL_CAS_DB` wins unconditionally if the env var is set.\n  - If set to `\"\"`, it returns an error: `CODALOTL_CAS_DB is empty`.\n  - If non-empty, it returns `filepath.Abs(CODALOTL_CAS_DB)`.\n  - In this path, `baseDir` is not validated and git is not inspected.\n  - A relative env value is resolved relative to the process working directory, not relative to `baseDir`.\n  - It does not create the directory.\n\n- Without `CODALOTL_CAS_DB`, `baseDir` is required.\n  - Empty `baseDir` returns `baseDir is empty`.\n  - `baseDir` is converted to an absolute path.\n  - If `baseDir` is an existing file, the search starts from its parent directory.\n  - If `baseDir` does not exist, it still walks upward from that path looking for a git root.\n\n- Git root selection:\n  - It walks upward from the absolute base dir and picks the nearest ancestor containing a `.git` filesystem entry.\n  - It accepts any `.git` entry that `os.Stat` can stat; it does not require `.git` to be a directory.\n  - Therefore normal repos with `.git/` and linked worktrees/submodules with a `.git` file are both treated as git roots.\n  - It does not shell out to `git`, does not resolve `git rev-parse --show-toplevel`, and does not redirect worktrees to the main repo’s common git dir.\n\n- Default CAS root:\n  - Once a git root is found, the returned root is:\n    - `\u003cgit-root\u003e/.codalotl/cas`\n\n- Fallback behavior:\n  - There is no non-git fallback such as home/cache/temp.\n  - If no ancestor contains `.git`, it returns an error like `no git root found for baseDir ...`.\n\nGrounding:\n- `internal/gocas/gocas.go:57-82` implements env override and root return.\n- `internal/gocas/gocas.go:280-300` implements nearest `.git` ancestor detection.\n- `internal/gocas/SPEC.md:15-22` documents the same high-level rule."}]},"additional_info":{"unix_timestamp":1778604908,"paths":["internal/gocas/SPEC.md","internal/gocas/gocas.go","internal/gocas/gocas_test.go"],"git_clean":false,"git_commit":"a1befc3f1118bc28f70ca4e4c4268bc2a242bb72","git_merge_base":"995ec50d0b375b3bea4e7f73fbcfc724270106ee"}}